		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Superbowl Action II 1/25/03<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.75)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711'>Michael "Longshot" Mendoza</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 26, 2003</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Surprisingly, this is the 1st constructed tournament I&#39;ve played in since the weekend TT became tourney legal.  In between that time I&#39;ve only done draft tournies.  Well, now is as good a time to play as any, considering the PSQ and Territorial for California is coming up, and other major tournies such as Vegas as well.  I did make some new decks; ringbound rangers & Nazgul, gandalf/gondor & uruk archery, uruk trackers & fellowship archery/choke, dwarves & Moria, and hobbits & uruks.  So I do some playtesting (thanks Davey) and pretty much decide on the gandalf/gondor deck.  But I&#39;m pretty fickle, and I&#39;m still not happy with the deck.  So after all the playtesting, I decide to rather use the hobbits.  I get advice on hobbits from a few people online & by phone, and decide to do hobbits, bidding 4 or 5 to go first, then using the site to pull Legolas, Dauntless Hunter (the only non-Shire fellowship card in the deck).<br />
<br />
If you think it sounds hokey, I&#39;m beginning to agree with you.  Anyways, I start all the common hobbits from the Fellowship set, and Frodo, Reluctant Adventurer using ATAR so he can become invisible and backstab some minions with that extra +2 strength.  The tournament is being run by Jeff Grein, at Superstars in Cupertino.  So I take the train from San Francisco down to the south bay and Jeff, in his infinite kindness, picks me up and takes me to the tourney from there.  14 players showed, so Jeff didn&#39;t play since he didn&#39;t want to create a bye.  What a nice guy.  It seemed to me that it was the usual crowd in attendance; the Greens, the Pages, Team Anduril, & a few new faces (at least to me they were new).  So we pay the $5 and start the 1st of 5 games.<br />
<br />
Game 1 v Magee Page&#39;s IsenOrcs/Southron Archery (starts Eowyn/Arwen)<br />
I was talking to Magee before we started the tourney, and she said she spent 4 hours making this deck.  So I was curious as to what it was, especially considering this is the 1st time I&#39;ll be playing her.  I bid 5 to her 2, and go first.  I get Legolas, use Sam to remove 2 burdens, and move to site 3, stealthing all the way but taking 3 archery wounds.  She plays Faramir w/sword & Asfaloth on Arwen, then stops at 2.  I play a sword and Sting, she plays an Isen Smith and Man archer, who exerts Sam (I have 2 Promises out), but the Smith takes 1 archery, and Frodo turns invisble and beats the Smith so he can&#39;t clip all my weapons.  I stop.  She moves to 3 without troubles.  I move to Helm&#39;s Gate, and she plays an Orc Overseer, among others.  But the Overseer takes an archery from Legolas, and Frodo becomes invisible and beats the Orc to prevent him from exhausting someone.  However, I have taken a significant amount of archery, and I could use a sanctuary about now, but I can&#39;t double-move.  Also, I am at 5 burdens.  Darn IsenOrcs are the perfect counter to hobbits, and I am seriously wondering if I was crazy to have thought hobbits could work.<br />
<br />
She moves to site 4 without troubles, and I am beginning to toss Shadow from my hand since she isn&#39;t double-moving and my hand is full of minions.  She stops, so I play Talent Not Being Seen (that&#39;s yet ANOTHER exertion!), move to site 6, while she plays Tower of Orthanc and an orc who wounds Legolas.  She moves to 5, where I try to get something going.  I do kill a companion (Eowyn I think).  But Arwen has Gwemegil and Asfaloth, & Faramir has his sword (remember this is at Helm&#39;s Gate), so they beat anyone I put down.  Magee decides to stop there though.  Meanwhile, I move to site 7, where all my unbound guys exert at King&#39;s Room.  Argh.  Magee plays some orcs and archers, and I have 4 vitality left out of all 5 of my companions when all is said and done.  And I am at 6 burdens.<br />
<br />
So she moves to site 6, stops.  I move to 8, adding 3 pool for the Tower, & she plays more orcs and archers, and by the end of the turn all my guys are exhausted.  So Promise is worthless, and I have NO way to heal.  So any archery (not to mention Enquea) now kills companions.  She moves to site 7 and stops, using Defend It and Hope with faramir to kill an Uruk.  So I move to site 9, giving lots of pool.  The only good thing for me was that she wasn&#39;t using the Palantir Chamber.  So she&#39;s playing minions, and I see orcs, and desert spearmen.  No archers.  And she only has 4 minions, so Frodo does not have to fight.  So I suppose all my other companions would have died, but we didn&#39;t go through it, we just called it right there.  Win (3 points).<br />
<br />
Best: Obviously I lucked out when she drew no archers at site 9.<br />
Worst: IsenOrcs are the perfect counter to hobbits.<br />
<br />
Game 2 v Jeremy Davis&#39; hobbits/Moria (starts defender +1 Sam)<br />
I bid 4 to his 0.  This time I get Cliffs of Emyn Muil in my hand, so I get to remove 2 burdens when I move, & I remove 2 with Sam.  I move to site 3 easily, so does he (just Sam and Frodo, OBH wearing ATAR).  I move to 4, he plays 2 Armories and an orc, who dies to archery.  Then he moves to site 4, and he stops as well.  I move to 5, he plays some more orcs, but he doesn&#39;t have pool left to play his Host Of Thousands.  Luckily I have 3 of my swords out, & we are at Helm&#39;s Gate.  So I take maybe 1 wound, and stop.  He moves, I play 2 uruks, but he has stealths, and stops.  Both his guys have swords, & he has 3 Promises out.  So I move to site 6 and stop without trouble.  He plays a 3rd Armory.  I have Bill and Talent, so I&#39;m subtracting 3 from the shadow number.  He easily moves to 6 and stops (he has Bill and Talent as well), but he also plays Rosie, Filibert, Bounder, and Party Guest.<br />
<br />
So I move to 7, he drops Swarms finally, and some orcs, but only Ancient Chieftain stacks (I use Escape to prevent others from winning).  I stop.  So he plays his 4th promise, & O Elbereth, so his guys are each 10 now.  All I have is 6 pool, enough for 2 power 9 uruks, but I do have a Savagery, so Sam takes a wound (he had Swiftly & Softly).  He stops, so I move to his Ring of Isengard, face some orcs, and he stacks a Scavenger.  Now I have a tough choice; to move again, or not to move?  I decide not to go for it, there are 12 cards left in my deck, and I figure I&#39;ll draw Saruman&#39;s Power any minute now (I even toss Saruman to get to it faster).  I reconcile….and yes!  There is the Power.  He moves to 8, I have 7 pool, play an Uruk, Power (1 Ambition out already), then Ambition, and another Uruk.  I overwhelm Sam with pumps (he had healed Rosie, not Bounder, figuring Promises would keep him out of overwhelming range), and now must stop.  So I make the move to 9, he plays 7 orcs on me, but I have There and Back Again and Severed His Bonds, so I easily survive.  I also had 4 Promises of my own out.  Win (6 points).<br />
<br />
Best: Legolas making his Hosts and conditions expensive.<br />
Worst: Free Moria Scouts.<br />
<br />
Game 3 v Phil Green&#39;s Uruk/Horn deck (starts Boromir/Merry)<br />
I bid 4 to his 3.  I play a sword on Merry, remove 2 burdens with Sam, get Legolas, and move to 2.  I stealth away from his uruk and stop.  He plays HTTWC w/sword (dmg +1 sword), & Greenleaf, along with the Horn on Boromir.  I play an uruk & ambition at site 2, he takes an archery, then Merry pumps Aragorn and beats my uruk (after I use my ambition).  He moves again to my Golden Hall, so Aragorn&#39;s sword is lost.  If necessary, I will take Aragorn down piece-by-piece, haha.  I draw 2 savageries, play a Troop.  He assigns the Troop to Aragorn (figuring I didn&#39;t have any savageries or I would have used them before), and I overwhelm Aragorn.  Merry dies on the fierce battle.  I move to site 3 without problems, although I have to hold Sting and a sword in my hand.<br />
<br />
Phil plays Faramir, Last Alliance, Galadriel and Orophin, then moves to site 4.  I play Power to kill the Alliance, then Orophin shoots down my uruk and he stops.  I play my weapons, move to 4 and stop.  He moves to my Deep of Helm, and I get a squad of uruks out and Saruman.  He survives alright though, since he put armor on Faramir and used the Horn.  Only Legolas died.  So he has Boromir, Faramir, and Frodo still, plus the allies.  I move to the Deep, facing a squad of uruks of my own, but as usual the stealths & Escape save me from taking any real damage, combined with the twilight denial of Talent and Bill.  Escape is like another twilight denial card, because they have to save 1 pool or the skirmish is canceled.  Phil plays healer Elrond and moves to site 6, he has no troubles.  I do the same.<br />
<br />
He moves to site 7 & here I drop a squad of guys again, including Saruman, regulars, and ravagers.  Elrond gets horned up, and Faramir takes some wounds with armor, and Frodo with Sting takes some wounds.  I move to site 7, and he must have had a hand full of shadow because he had lots of minions.  I took some wounds, but no one died.  Then he plays Last Alliance on Faramir, moved armor to Boromir, & moved to site 8.  I dropped another 3 uruks and Saruman.  So he calls up Elrond & Orophin, uses Sentinels to kill my Ambition, and the 2 allies and Faramir all fight.  But he does the Orophin skirmish first (he had a wound), so he dies.  Now Faramir loses to his uruk, and dies.  Only Elrond wins.  Thus, Elrond, Boromir, and Frodo must now fight, so Boromir dies as well.  So now Frodo is all alone, except for allies who won&#39;t heed his call for help.  And so when he moves to site 9 Frodo is killed.  Win (9 points).<br />
<br />
Best: Hobbits got revenge on Phil, since Phil was the only one to beat my last hobbit deck at a tournament.<br />
Worst: None really.<br />
<br />
Game 4 v Alfred Dong&#39;s archery choke/uruks (starts Greenleaf/Arwen)<br />
Alfred is part of Team Anduril, and the only other undefeated player.  For some stupid reason I decide to bid low because burdens were hurting me.  So I bid 2, he bids 2.  He wins the toss, and goes first.  Darn, no Legolas for me this game.  Opening hand….Legolas AND Cliffs!  Huge.  So he plays Faramir and HTTWC, kills my uruks with archery, & moves to 3 easily.  This is a deck very similar to the deck I used the first weekend TT came out (and went 5-0 with).  Its very solid, and one of the decks I&#39;ve been developing counter-measures for.  But its hard to do without going overboard.<br />
<br />
Anyways, I move to my Derndingle (with no wounds or burdens, there&#39;s a first), he plays an Ambition & an uruk, who takes an archery, then I stealth.  I move again, he plays another Ambition & uruk, who takes an archery.  Then he plays savagery on an uruk, so I use Cliffs to kill it, then he plays savagery on the other uruk, I use stealth.  Then he takes the uruk away (puts him in the discard pile) and clears the pool (there was 1 in there from my stealth) and I say &quot;hold on I might want to move again.&quot;  Don&#39;t forget about Derndingle.  Then he realizes the uruk was fierce and wants me to fight him again.  Jeff comes over and agrees with him, and allows him to go all the way back to the skirmish phase so I have to fight him again.  That&#39;s wrong.  I say we&#39;re in regroup phase; he DISCARDED the uruk.  So I assign the uruk to Pippin (he has Escape), I USE Escape, and THEN they put the pool back, and put 2 in.  I say, &quot;No, there was only 1 in there.&quot;  That way Pippin could exert 4 times to cancel the skirmish.  But Jefeasterlingrees with Alfred AGAIN (and if you go back and add it up, there should only be 1 in there, although at the time we didn&#39;t go back and do the math).  Fine, I say &quot;ok, I want to at least change assignments since you have now added pool.&quot;  But Jeff doesn&#39;t let me, so I have to use my last stealth and I have to stop.  I can&#39;t even take back using Escape, as if I&#39;d use it with pool in there.  So I&#39;ve taken wounds on Pippin for nothing.  If I hadn&#39;t had Legolas and Cliffs to save me those exertions at site 1, I would have been very mad cuz I couldn&#39;t have healed all those wounds on Pippin.  But it was fine since Pippin would be healed.<br />
<br />
So Alfred moves and stops at site 4.  I do the same easily.  Then he moves to my Deep of Helm, where I have 2 savageries & Saruman and some cheap uruks (Regulars, Ravagers) and kill Arwen, Legolas, and Faramir.  I move to the Deep and he gets a squad on me, but I have stealths and Escape (I make sure to use Escape first, before I add pool from stealths).  He moves to site 6 and is just fine, I follow and stop.  But when he moves to site 7 I get 2 uruks out.  Alfred uses his Gondor Bowmen & 1 PATHS to kill the uruks.  I move to 7 and stop, I have 4 promises out so Frodo is pretty tough to beat.  He moves to my Vale, I add some pool, play Saruman and 3 uruks.  I take some more archery from the rest of his Bowmen, Frodo fights 2 exhausted uruks & plays PATHS, but I only save 1 uruk with Saruman, Frodo takes some wounds.  Aragorn dies, and Filibert cancels the fierce skirmish.  I move to the Vale and stop, because my hand is full of Shadow so I don&#39;t want to risk losing.  He moves, I play some uruks and he has not even a PATHS.  Win (12 points)<br />
<br />
Best: Winning again.<br />
Worst: I still think Jeff and Alfred got the call wrong at site 3, but it worked out since otherwise my Deep of Helm probably would not have come out.<br />
<br />
Game 5 v Dave Kemner&#39;s archery choke/uruks (starts Greenleaf/Arwen)<br />
Dave is also a part of Team Anduril, and apparently using the same deck as Alfred, although it did have some differences.  It was more like my deck I think though.  Well I wised up and bid 4 again, so I went first.  He bid 2.  I move to site 3 easily, and I got Cliffs in my opening hand again (I play 2).  Dave plays Faramir and HTTWC.  But when he gets to site 3 I have a Troop, and he pairs him up against Aragorn.  I play 2 savageries and &#39;Gorn is overwhelmed.  Then I prove I am an idiot because I pick up the Troop and discard him.  Dave doesn&#39;t tell me until the end of the game that I forgot the fierce skirmish.  Oh well.  I move to site 4, no problem.  He does the same.<br />
<br />
I move to Deep of Helm, face a squad of uruks, but stealths, Promises, and Escape save me from losing anyone, and from even taking much damage.  Plus I had Talent out to subtract pool.  I stop.  He moves to Deep, and he uses Sting to see my hand.  I have an Ambition and Savagery.  I play Saruman and 3 uruks, so Arwen, Legolas, and Faramir have to fight in both skirmishes and they all die, otherwise Frodo would get overwhelmed (unless he had been using ATAR).  I move to 6, stop.  Then he moves to 6 and Frodo gets overwhelmed by an uruk.  Win (15 points).<br />
<br />
Best: The uruks have just been beating down today, at least in my last 3 games.<br />
Worst: Forgetting my fierce, power 17 Troop at site 3.  I&#39;m such a champ.<br />
<br />
Alfred ends up at 4-1, taking 2nd place, and Phil has an amazingly high opposition total, losing only to Alfred and I, so he gets 3rd place at 3-2.  Phil also makes some witty remark about how I sell my soul to the devil to win with these hokey decks.  And he says, &quot;I thought you can only sell your soul once.&quot;  So I reply with &quot;I sell OTHER people&#39;s souls, not my own.  I barter in souls&quot;  Haha.  I guess the moral of the story is this: Its better to be lucky than good.  Thanks for reading.<br />
<br />
Props to:<br />
Jeff & his wife for their hospitality, for the rides, for running the tournament, & for putting up with me in general.<br />
Everyone who helped me with my deck & playtested with me.<br />
Team Anduril for playing Trek.<br />
Whoever won the multiplayer tourney in southern Cal.<br />
Everyone who read this, and liked it.<br />
Tampa Bay for winning the Super Bowl.  I was sad when they beat the Niners.<br />
<br />
Slops to:<br />
The store for running out of TT packs.<br />
Weekends for being really short. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=4178&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
